# supplychain-kit suppression file
#
# One rule per line. Use `#` for comments.
#
# Format:  <rule_id_glob>  [path:<glob>]  [package:<glob>]  [fingerprint:<value>]  [reason:<text>]
#
# Tokens after the rule ID combine with AND. Rules on different lines combine with OR.
# Suppressed findings are marked VEX "not_affected" — they stay in findings.json
# with a `suppressed_by` audit trail, but drop out of summaries and --fail-on.
#
# Examples:

# Accept a specific CVE as a known false positive
# CVE-2023-12345

# Suppress a Semgrep rule only in legacy code
# semgrep.tainted-sql  path:internal/legacy/*.go  reason:legacy module, scheduled for removal 2026-Q3

# Drop all findings for an unmaintained dev-only dependency
# *  package:dead-package  reason:unmaintained, only used in integration tests

# Exact-fingerprint suppression (most precise — won't drift when the rule changes)
# *  fingerprint:a1b2c3d4e5f6...
